    "To complement the description of the small J/t 0 regime, we plot the time-evolution of the electronic quasimomentum distribution function n k for J/t 0 = 0.9 in Fig. 3(a).",
    "The conduction electron starts with k 0 = π/2 due to our initial condition from Eq.",
    "At short times, n k retains a peak at π/2 which then quickly decays.",
    "The momentum occupations redistribute into two distinct peaks: one just below π/2 and another one above -π/2, located specifically at k = π/2 -J/4t 0 and k = -π/2 + J/4t 0.",
    "Since these peaks are sharp and far away from k = 0, the steady state does not correspond to a thermal state."
